commit.message:
Fix icon filename

Closes: https://www.grisbi.org/bugsreports/view.php?id=2298

Fix a crash on import with duplicate transactions

The problem created a crash only on Windows but the code was wrong also
for GNU/Linux and macOS.

Closes: https://www.grisbi.org/bugsreports/view.php?id=2292

AppVeyor: update libofx on Windows builds

Update from 0.9.15 to 0.10.9.

No problem with the old version but it should not harm to upgrade.
Install German categories in de/ instead of de_DE/

github actions: use actions/checkout@v4

build (macos-latest)
Node.js 16 actions are deprecated. Please update the following actions to use Node.js 20: actions/checkout@v3. For more information see: https://github.blog/changelog/2023-09-22-github-actions-transitioning-from-node-16-to-node-20/.
github acions: ignore build warning on macOS

Add missing categories for fr

The patch in 158fd5cca363ecb0097ca0b895566c54e326accc was incomplete
Missing files:
- plan-associatif-simplifie.cgsb
- plan-comptable.cgsb
Default/English: Add "Internet" in "Housing" category
French: add "Internet" in "Logement" category

Move German categories into de

No more 2 options de_AT and de_DE. The standard categories are now
available when languge is set to "de".

I also removed de_AT/kontenplan.cgsb as suggested by Martin Stromberger:
" Well kontenplan.cgsb is for small companies - not for private persons.
This file is rather old and I don't think that this file is really used
by someone. "

Move French categories from fr_FR into fr

Fixes https://www.grisbi.org/bugsreports/view.php?id=2287

Now the "Plan comptable associatif simplifié" and "Plan comptable
associatif" are available when the language is set to "fr", not just
"fr_FR".

D:\a\_temp\msys64\ucrt64\bin\msgfmt.exe: cannot locate ITS rules for grisbi.metainfo.xml.in

commit.message:
Add the developer_name tag to the metainfo

As required by: https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-app-authors/appdata-guidelines/#name-summary-and-developer-name

Signed-off-by: Aurélien Bompard <aurelien@bompard.org>

Remove leftover intltool markers

According to https://wiki.gnome.org/MigratingFromIntltoolToGettext, the
underscores markers must be removed from the xml files that need to be
translated.

Signed-off-by: Aurélien Bompard <aurelien@bompard.org>
github action: build Windows version

4350b22cf6c55034a5b5470b07e498736fe0fda4 (Apr 2 2021)

Fix compiler warning

On Windows we had:
gsb_locale.c:282:30: error: unused variable 'tmp_language' [-Werror=unused-variable]
  282 |                 const gchar *tmp_language = NULL;
      |                              ^~~~~~~~~~~~

Correctly set user_default_dir on Windows

This bugs was introduced by me in
28e0e803e0ab6005c46ff6c94f41160f6dd975c8 included since Grisbi 3.0.0

This caused "permission denied" errors when saving the file (on Windows
only).

Fixes: https://www.grisbi.org/bugsreports/view.php?id=2283
